document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    const menuToggle = document.querySelector('.menu-toggle');
    const nav = document.querySelector('header nav');

    // Toggle mobile menu
    if (menuToggle && nav) {
        menuToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
            nav.classList.toggle('active');
        });
    }
});```

### Final Steps:
1.  **Add Images:** Find some images for your courses (you can use a site like [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/)), name them appropriately (e.g., `web-dev.jpg`, `data-science.jpg`), and place them in the `/images` folder you created.
2.  **Open in Browser:** Open the `index.html` file in your web browser to see your website live! You can navigate between the home and courses pages.
